index 28bcbd9e..7c0286af 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -107,3 +107,11 @@ If used for academic research, please cite:
 
 D. Petrisko, F. Gilani, M. Wyse, D. C. Jung, S. Davidson, P. Gao, C. Zhao, Z. Azad, S. Canakci, B. Veluri, T. Guarino, A. J. Joshi, M. Oskin, M. B. Taylor, ["BlackParrot: An Agile Open Source RISC-V Multicore for Accelerator SoCs"](https://taylor-bsg.github.io/papers/BlackParrot_IEEE_Micro_2020.pdf), in *IEEE Micro Special Issue on Agile and Open-Source Hardware*, July/August, 2020. doi: 10.1109/MM.2020.2996145
 
+## RUNNING MULTITHREAD
+To run with multithreading copy the [kylee.riscv](kylee.riscv) into the path `sdk/prog/risv-tests`. 
+
+Then, `cd bp_top/syn/` and run `make build_dump.sc sim_dump.sc SUITE=bp-tests PROG=kylee CFG=e_bp_multicore_1_multithread_2_cfg`. If you want to look at the waveforms from this test, you can then run `make wave.sc SUITE=bp-tests PROG=kylee CFG=e_bp_multicore_1_multithread_2_cfg`
+
+If you want to know what the multithread test does, check [kylee.c](kylee.c). 
+
+NOTE: I have only enabled 2 thread configuration (CFG) so do NOT try switching to any thread except for 0 or 1. I'm happy to add configs for additional threads but we do not check that you're switching to a valid thread so make sure your code is safe. 
